BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KoP7G6PaLq1p-tRcN51ts
SUMMARY:Screen Printing Open Session
DTSTAMP:20260326T022926Z
DTSTART:20260616T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:You MUST take the SP 101: Intro to Vera's Screen Print Studio c
	lass before you can sign up for an Open Session\n\nVera’s screen print stu
	dio offers four-hour Open Sessions where individuals who have completed th
	e introductory class may use our screen print lab to work on their own pro
	jects. Our Open Sessions are looked over by a volunteer moderator\, who ca
	n provide you with advice and guidance for anything taught in our Screen P
	rinting 101 class. We offer three different kinds of tickets at Open Sessi
	ons: Vacuum Table for paper and other flat media\, T-shirt Press for shirt
	s\, tote bags and other fabrics\, and Screen prep for just screen preparat
	ion. Each ticket is limited to two. If the ticket you are looking for is s
	old out\, please add yourself to the waitlist so you can be notified when 
	a ticket becomes available.\n\nFor Open Sessions\, Vera provides:\n\n- Ren
	table screens\n- Emulsion and emulsion remover\n- Squegees\n- Basic tools 
	like spatulas\, rulers\, tape\, etc.\n\nParticipants must provide their ow
	n:\n\n- Substrate (paper\, t-shirts\, etc)\n- Water based ink\n\nVera does
	 not allow the use of non-water based inks at our studio\, as our studio i
	s not set up to safely process non-water based ink.\n\nIf you have any que
	stions\, please email matt@theveraproject.org.\n\nFAQ\n\n1\\. Can Vera pri
	nt a transparent stencil for me?\n\nYes — You must send us your stencil at
	 least 24 hours before the start of your session. Your file must be a .PDF
	\, no larger than 12" x 18"\, and ready to print. Vera cannot make any edi
	ts to your file. Stencils are $5 each and can be paid via Debit/Credit whe
	n you arrive.\n\nIf you are not interested in getting a stencil printed at
	 Vera\, you can print your own on transparency at a FedEx or similar print
	 service location.\n\n2\\. What if I need direct assistance on my projects
	?\n\nOur moderators are trained to assist with any topics covered in the S
	P 101 class offered at Vera. While some may be able to give you basic advi
	ce on your project\, they are not expected to ask as a direct instructor. 
	If you have a project where you would like one-on-one guidance\, please re
	ach out to matt@theveraproject.org to request private tutoring.\n\n3\\. I 
	really want to use your studio during an Open Session\, but there are no s
	lots available?\n\nOur studio is in high demand\, so we apologize if our O
	pen Session is sold out — We have limited space in the studio and several 
	events every day at Vera\, so it can be difficult for us to find more time
	 for Open Sessions. If you're interested in booking the studio outside of 
	Open Sessions\, please email matt@theveraproject.org to discuss private re
	ntal rates and availability.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/vf3f1194fc97
URL:https://link.dice.fm/vf3f1194fc97
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:glQLpPRbz10hNTEAeYB0d
SUMMARY:SY 101: Basics of Electronic Audio
DTSTAMP:20260326T022926Z
DTSTART:20260618T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Interested in learning more about synthesizers? In this informa
	tive 2-hour workshop\, our instructor will provide you with a brief histor
	y of synthesis and a detailed breakdown of Basic Subtractive Patching!\n\n
	*The use of a laptop and headphones are required to participate in this cl
	ass. You will need to download the free software VCV Rack. Vera has a limi
	ted amount of laptops that we can provide on a first-come-first-serve basi
	s to our members. If you do have your own laptop\, we would appreciate if 
	you used your own\, so we can provide laptops to those who may not have on
	e. If you would like to request a laptop\, please email yewon@theveraproje
	ct.org. You will also need to download a couple files for this workshop. T
	hese files will be sent 24 hours before the class.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm
	/X999e254b0f1
URL:https://link.dice.fm/X999e254b0f1
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Ss2PBprBpm8iFnIujNMVR
SUMMARY:LS 101: Basics of Live Sound
DTSTAMP:20260326T022926Z
DTSTART:20260618T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Basics of Live Sound is a 2-hour introduction to live audio eng
	ineering and an orientation to Vera Project’s methods and equipment. Topic
	s covered include an introduction to microphones and mic placement\, signa
	l paths\, stands\, cables\, DI’s\, snake\, sub-snakes and etiquette for wo
	rking with bands. This class is designed for both the novices and experts 
	of all ages and will give an overview of signal flow and setting up small 
	PAs\, in addition to the basic requirements for being part of the Vera sou
	nd team at shows. Discover why the accommodating\, open minded “Vera Attit
	ude” of show production is appreciated worldwide!\n\nThis class is a prere
	quisite for advanced audio classes at Vera and Sound Runner shifts at Vera
	 Project show. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engineering volunte
	er shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and outside of the 
	venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-related educationa
	l programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships!\n\nhttps://link.
	dice.fm/Bbfdd5dafd0d
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Bbfdd5dafd0d
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8Ph93AUeFQU2R3lNGOlSc
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to VERA's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260326T022926Z
DTSTART:20260618T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at VERA’s screen printing studio: From hand-draw
	ing a stencil on transparency\, coating and burning a screen\, to pulling 
	your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop layout\, equipment
	\, and culture. Learn techniques for creating screens\, terminology\, and 
	more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. Students will walk away
	 with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color paper prints\, and thei
	r own print of a special Vera design\, specific to the 101 class.\n\nThis 
	class is a prerequisite for 200-level classes at VERA\, as well as access 
	to Open Sessions to work on your own projects in VERA’s screen printing st
	udio.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/e7b5187e4af1
URL:https://link.dice.fm/e7b5187e4af1
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
